      "skills" : null,
      "note" : [ {
        "text" : "The Taliban severely repressed women’s rights. From 1992 until 2001, women could not interact with men outside of their families. In public, they had to be accompanied by a male relative and cover themselves from head to toe in a burqa. Women’s education was forbidden and they were often deprived of access to health care. Forced marriages were common.",
