      "skills" : null,
      "note" : [ {
        "text" : "Since the fall of the Taliban, rebalancing gender equality has progressed slowly. Burqas are still common, though not required by law. The 2004 Afghan constitution requires equal treatment of women under the law. However, the constitution also emphasizes that no law can run contrary to Islam, leaving women’s rights up to religious interpretation in practice.",
